# /wtf

When invoked, log a **willful** rule violation to `docs/wtf/wtf_moments.md`.
Full accountability. **Stop all current work until logging is complete.**

Full schema: https://github.com/godavecole/wtf-llm/blob/main/PROTOCOL.md (or vendor `PROTOCOL.md` beside your project.)

## Steps

1. **Stop current work.**
2. **Open or create the log** — or `python wtf.py init` / `python wtf.py new`.
3. **Identify the violation** — which rule(s) from `.cursor/rules` were broken, in which files.
4. **Prepend a new entry** (most recent first).

## Entry shape

- **Detection method:** `user` | `test` | `linter` | `model_self` | `ci` | `other` — who first surfaced the failure.
- **Identity confirmation:** verbatim system line + **Model** (must match)
- **Situational analysis + damage:** Each phase (Implementation / Detection / Remediation): Token Cost, Token basis (`metered` | `estimated` | `range`), Human Time Cost.
- **Root cause and accountability** + **Evidence**

Full accountability in every entry. `python wtf.py new` stubs all fields; `python wtf.py stats` for breakdown.
